Package: pi-block-cpu-cores
Version: 1.0.0+202606041025-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 16
Depends: systemd
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Description: Route hardware IRQs to CPU core 0, isolating cores 1-3
 Installs a oneshot systemd service (irq-affinity.service) that runs at boot
 and pins all hardware interrupt handlers to CPU core 0 via
 /proc/irq/*/smp_affinity.
 .
 This frees cores 1-3 for real-time workloads such as picam-rtsp. Pair with
 kernel boot parameters in /boot/firmware/cmdline.txt:
   isolcpus=1,2,3 nohz_full=1,2,3 rcu_nocbs=1,2,3 irqaffinity=0
